Package com.CloudOfficePrint.RenderElements

Class AOPChart

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.CloudOfficePrint.RenderElements.RenderElement
      • com.CloudOfficePrint.RenderElements.AOPChart
  • public class AOPChart
extends RenderElement
    Supported in Word, Excel and Powerpoint templates. This class represent AOP charts (including the data and style). The chart in the template can be styled through MS Office or LibreOffice as an alternative to passing the style options as a part of the input data. This allows the use of style options we do not support, but moves the chart styling from the data to the template. This may case some difficulties, e.g. : loops containing a chart with different style on each iteration would not be possible using this tag.

        Represent an AOP chart (including data and style). If you don't want te specify some parameters, use null as argument.
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the chart for the tag.
        xData - ArrayList(String) of the data of the x-axis. Format : ["day 1", "day 2", "day 3", "day 4", "day 5"] or [{"value": "day 1"}, {"value": "day 2"}, {"value": "day 3"}, {"value": "day 4"}, {"value": "day 5"}]
        yData - HashMap(Name of the serie), ArrayList(y-data) data in the same format as xData.
        title - Title of the chart.
        xTitle - Title of the x-axis.
        yTitle - Title of the y-axis.
        y2Title - Title of the second x-axis.
        x2Title - Title of the second y-axis.
        aopChartDateOptions - Date options for the chart.
